snippet.textDisplay:
"2 years of retainers? I never even had that long with retainers!"

That's when I remembered I hadn't wore them in 7 months.
No seriously. I can't wear them anymore. I recently got a crown instead of filling which my top retainer refuses to fit anymore, and since I haven't been wearing them my teeth hurt when i put the bottom on so i was like, "Okay then-"
Even worse, the crown is more sensitive than the rest of my teeth so I can't really spit out cold things. I can eat\drink them, my mouth covers it, but nothing is blocking the tooth when i rinse my mouth every time i brush my teeth.

Don't get me started on braces

snippet.textDisplay: I know how you felt with that appointment. I had to get my wisdom teeth taken out a few months ago. All 4 all at once. I was so scared and freaked out about it for like a month before the appointment. They actually knocked me out which I was really scared about on top of the teeth coming out. But when I woke up and had to move from the chair to a waiting room type thing with a blood pressure wrap on my arm and ice wrapped around my face because I looked like a squirrel that had too many nuts in it's mouth. They went to the waiting room to get my boyfriend because I couldn't walk because of the meds they used to knock me out I couldn't feel anything my entire mouth was numb. But after a couple hours and rest once I got home I ended up feeling relived that it was done and I won't have to do it ever again, and honestly I felt stupid for freaking out as much as I did before the appointment. To anyone who has to deal with this, don't stress about it. It's not a big deal you will be fine! Recovering will be fine too and honestly you could stay in bed the whole time which is what I did.

snippet.textDisplay:
So I have a similar story re; pulling my teeth out. When I was 12 I had this one baby tooth that had been wiggling for like a year? So they took some xrays and decided that the two next to it had pinned it in place so the adult tooth decided to come down through my hard palette. They sent me to see a specialist who told me in detail how they would break apart the baby tooth, push aside the bully adults and drill a hole in the roof of my mouth to move the adult back into its lane before sealing it up with stitches and 5 years of braces.

After having just recovered from a tonsillectomy earlier that year I got back to the car with a game plan in mind. When mom asked how I was feeling about it, I reached up and RIPPED the baby out of my mouth with no hesitation. I spent the next month widening the gap and pushing the bump on the roof of my mouth where the adult was to force it back into place. As an adult my dentist was very surprised at how well it worked.

Point being is that I too had a fear fuelled moment of super human strength and that your mom is super cool for paying you. I didnt even get to pick out an extra snack for all the money I saved her!
